"Suture #1 - Found"; "Suture #2 - Breakthrough"; "Suture #3 - Passage". Acrilic and oil on canvas, 138x85cm.

There are wounds we do not notice, in the moment they're inflicted to us. We forget them in a corner of our souls, leaving their healing to fate and time. By re-opening a scar, we take back the power over it: the power to close it at our conditions, to learn from it, forgive ourselves, to turn a cut into a suture, and finally, truly heal.

#painting #abstract #oiloncanvas #scars #suture

"Friendly Ghosts"

Acrylic and oil on paper on canvas, 115x100cm

Around the end of 2017, I was feeling old. Tired. A bunchful of fragile bones kept together, walking towards something. Yet I wasn't alone, my friendly ghost was watching over me, leading me all the way to his homeland, meant to be mine too.

#surrealism #shamanism #spiritual #painting #journey #ghosts #art

"Lethe - Light to ghosts"

Acrylic and oil on canvas, 90x110cm.

Dismembered and newly forged, forgetting, forgotten. I bring light, I am light to ghosts.

"Phantom hyde and seek"

Acrylic and oil on paper.

Me and my friendly ghosts, playing hyde and seek. Seeking a way out of our land, hold me in their adoring grip.

#surrealism #art #painting #vision #dream

"Inis Mona - Beyond my grave"

Acrylic and oil on canvas, 110x90cm.

One year ago, I believe I died. It actually felt much better than carrying my bones around, living. I died, found a land of ghosts and became their queen. I floated peacefully, enjoying my afterdeath, before facing the pain of being reborn.
 I call this land Inis Mona.

#surrealism #shamanism #painter  #inspiration #art #vision

"The Apprentice Sorcerer - No more afraid"

#surrealism #painting #painter #art #shamanism #visions

"Suture #1"
Acrylic and oil on paper, 94x80cm "It's been some days I've been waking up wishing to crack-open my head to see if my monsters were still there. Yet, when I did it, I only found suture marks." #abstract #painting #painter #art
